# Credit Default Risk Prediction
## Dataset

This project uses the **Home Credit Default Risk** dataset from Kaggle.

- Source: https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/home-credit-default-risk  
- The dataset contains information about loan applicants, including:
  - Demographics (age, income, family status)
  - Financial history
  - Credit behavior
  - Previous loan records

## Problem

The objective is to predict whether a client will have payment difficulties (default) based on historical and behavioral data.

## Challenges

- Missing values
- Imbalanced dataset
- Large number of features (100+ variables)
## Overview
This project predicts customer default risk using machine learning.

## Techniques
- Data cleaning
- Feature engineering
- Logistic Regression / Random Forest

## Results
- Accuracy: 76%

## Tools
Python, pandas, scikit-learn
